l+and+Terrestrial%2C+and+their+Use%5D&amp;rft.date=1627&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Francofvrti+ad+Moenvm+%5BFrankfurt+am+Main%2C+Germany%5D&amp;rft.pub=Typis+%26+sumptibus+VVechelianorum%2C+apud+Danielem+%26+Dauidem+Aubrios+%26+Clementem+Schleichium+%5BPrinted+and+paid+for+by+the+Wechelians%2C+by+Daniel+and+David+Aubrios+and+Clement+Schleich%5D&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F23625532&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (in Latin), <a href="/wiki/Ternion" class="mw-redirect" title="Ternion">duodecimo</a>.</li>\n<li><b>10th printing</b>: <cite id="CITEREFHues1638" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1638), <i>A Learned Treatise of Globes, both C\xc5\x93lestiall and Terrestriall: With their Severall Uses. Written first in Latine, by Mr Robert Hues: And by him so Published. Afterward Illustrated with Notes, by Io. Isa. Pontanus. And now Lastly made English, for the Benefit of the Unlearned by John Chilmead M<sup>r</sup>A of Christ-Church in Oxon</i>, London: Printed by the assigne of T[homas] P[urfoot] for P[hilemon] Stephens and C[hristopher] Meredith, and are to be sold at their shop at the Golden Lion in Pauls-Church-yard, <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/165905181">165905181</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=A+Learned+Treatise+of+Globes%2C+both+C%C5%93lestiall+and+Terrestriall%3A+With+their+Severall+Uses.+Written+first+in+Latine%2C+by+Mr+Robert+Hues%3A+And+by+him+so+Published.+Afterward+Illustrated+with+Notes%2C+by+Io.+Isa.+Pontanus.+And+now+Lastly+made+English%2C+for+the+Benefit+of+the+Unlearned+by+John+Chilmead+M%3Csup%3Er%3C%2Fsup%3EA+of+Christ-Church+in+Oxon&amp;rft.date=1638&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Printed+by+the+assigne+of+T%5Bhomas%5D+P%5Burfoot%5D+for+P%5Bhilemon%5D+Stephens+and+C%5Bhristopher%5D+Meredith%2C+and+are+to+be+sold+at+their+shop+at+the+Golden+Lion+in+Pauls-Church-yard&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F165905181&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-41" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-41">[41]</a></sup></li>\n<li><b>11th printing</b>: A Latin version by Jodocus Hondius and John Isaac Pontanus appeared in London in 1659. Octavo.<sup id="cite_ref-42" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-42">[42]</a></sup></li>\n<li><b>12th printing</b>: <cite id="CITEREFHuesJohn_Isaac_Pontanus1659" class="citation">Hues, Robert; John Isaac Pontanus (1659), <i>A Learned Treatise of Globes, both C\xc5\x93lestiall and Terrestriall with their Several Uses&#160;..</i>, London: Printed by J.S. for Andrew Kemb, and are to be sold at his shop&#160;..., <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/11947725">11947725</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.au=John+Isaac+Pontanus&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=A+Learned+Treatise+of+Globes%2C+both+C%C5%93lestiall+and+Terrestriall+with+their+Several+Uses+..&amp;rft.date=1659&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Printed+by+J.S.+for+Andrew+Kemb%2C+and+are+to+be+sold+at+his+shop+...&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F11947725&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>, octavo. Collection of <a href="/wiki/Yale_University_Library" title="Yale University Library">Yale University Library</a>.</li>\n<li><b>13th printing</b>: <cite id="CITEREFHues1663" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1663), <i>Tractatus de globis coelesti et terrestri eorumque usu ac de novo recognitus multisq[ue] observationibus opportun\xc3\xa8 illustratus ac passim auctus, opera et studio Johannis Isacii Pontani&#160;...; adjicitur Breviarium totius orbis terrarum Petri Bertii&#160;... [Treatise on Globes Celestial and Terrestrial and their Use, Collected Anew and Suitably Illustrated with Many Observations and Enlarged Throughout, by the Effort and Devotion of John Isaac Pontanus&#160;... A Brief Account of the Whole Globe is Added by Peter Bertius&#160;...]</i>, Oxford: Excudebat [printed by] W.H., impensis [at the expense of] Ed. Forrest, <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/13197923">13197923</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatus+de+globis+coelesti+et+terrestri+eorumque+usu+ac+de+novo+recognitus+multisq%5Bue%5D+observationibus+opportun%C3%A8+illustratus+ac+passim+auctus%2C+opera+et+studio+Johannis+Isacii+Pontani+...%3B+adjicitur+Breviarium+totius+orbis+terrarum+Petri+Bertii+...+%5BTreatise+on+Globes+Celestial+and+Terrestrial+and+their+Use%2C+Collected+Anew+and+Suitably+Illustrated+with+Many+Observations+and+Enlarged+Throughout%2C+by+the+Effort+and+Devotion+of+John+Isaac+Pontanus+...+A+Brief+Account+of+the+Whole+Globe+is+Added+by+Peter+Bertius+...%5D&amp;rft.date=1663&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Excudebat+%5Bprinted+by%5D+W.H.%2C+impensis+%5Bat+the+expense+of%5D+Ed.+Forrest&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F13197923&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (in Latin).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<dl>\n<dd>The Hakluyt Society\'s reprint of the English version was itself published as:\n<ul>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHuesMarkham1889" class="citation">Hues, Robert; <a href="/wiki/Clements_Markham" title="Clements Markham">Markham, Clements R., ed.</a> (1889), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/?id=HYfE8Z8PrAgC"><i>Tractatus de globis et eorum usu: A Treatise Descriptive of the Globes Constructed by Emery Molyneux and Published in 1592 [Hakluyt Society, 1st ser., pt. II, no. 79a]</i></a>, London: <a href="/wiki/Hakluyt_Society" title="Hakluyt Society">Hakluyt Society</a>, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8337-1759-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-8337-1759-7">978-0-8337-1759-7</a>, <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/149869781">149869781</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.au=Markham%2C+Clements+R.%2C+ed.&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatus+de+globis+et+eorum+usu%3A+A+Treatise+Descriptive+of+the+Globes+Constructed+by+Emery+Molyneux+and+Published+in+1592+%26%2391%3BHakluyt+Society%2C+1st+ser.%2C+pt.+II%2C+no.+79a%26%2393%3B&amp;rft.date=1889&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8337-1759-7&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Hakluyt+Society&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2F%3Fid%3DHYfE8Z8PrAgC&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F149869781&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span><span class="citation-comment" style="display:none; color:#33aa33; margin-left:0.3em">CS1 maint: Extra text: authors list (<a href="/wiki/Category:CS1_maint:_Extra_text:_authors_list" title="Category:CS1 maint: Extra text: authors list">link</a>)</span>.</li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:172px;"><a href="/wiki/File:RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg/170px-RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg" width="170" height="232" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg/255px-RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg/340px-RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1465" data-file-height="2000" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:RobertHues-TractaetGlobe-1623.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nThe title page of a 1623 Dutch version of Hues\' <i>Tractatus de globis</i></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The following works also are, or appear to be, versions of <i>Tractatus de globis et eorum usu</i>, though they are not mentioned by Markham:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHues1623" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1623), <i>Tractaet ofte Handelinge van het gebruyck der Hemelscher ende Aertscher Globe: In\'t Latyn eerst beschreven door Robertvm Hves, Mathematicum / en nu in Nederduytsch over-geset en met diversche nieuwe Verklaringen en Figuren vermeerdert en verciert / oock vele disputable questien gesolveert, door Iohannem Isacivm Pontanvm, Medicyn, en Professor der Philosophie inde vermaerde Schole te Harderwyck [Treatise or Essays on the Use of the Heavenly and Earthly Globe: First Described in Latin by Robert Hues, Mathematician / and now Translated into Dutch, and Expanded and Decorated with New Clarifications and Figures / also many Disputable Questions Solved, by John Isaac Pontanus, Physician and Professor of Philosophy of the renowned <a href="/wiki/University_of_Harderwijk" title="University of Harderwijk">School in Harderwijk</a>]</i>, Amsterdam: <a href="/wiki/Jodocus_Hondius" title="Jodocus Hondius">Iudocus Hondius</a>, woonende op den Dam [living on the <a href="/wiki/Dam_Square" title="Dam Square">Dam</a>], <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/51084257">51084257</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractaet+ofte+Handelinge+van+het+gebruyck+der+Hemelscher+ende+Aertscher+Globe%3A+In%27t+Latyn+eerst+beschreven+door+Robertvm+Hves%2C+Mathematicum+%2F+en+nu+in+Nederduytsch+over-geset+en+met+diversche+nieuwe+Verklaringen+en+Figuren+vermeerdert+en+verciert+%2F+oock+vele+disputable+questien+gesolveert%2C+door+Iohannem+Isacivm+Pontanvm%2C+Medicyn%2C+en+Professor+der+Philosophie+inde+vermaerde+Schole+te+Harderwyck+%26%2391%3BTreatise+or+Essays+on+the+Use+of+the+Heavenly+and+Earthly+Globe%3A+First+Described+in+Latin+by+Robert+Hues%2C+Mathematician+%2F+and+now+Translated+into+Dutch%2C+and+Expanded+and+Decorated+with+New+Clarifications+and+Figures+%2F+also+many+Disputable+Questions+Solved%2C+by+John+Isaac+Pontanus%2C+Physician+and+Professor+of+Philosophy+of+the+renowned+School+in+Harderwijk%26%2393%3B&amp;rft.date=1623&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Amsterdam&amp;rft.pub=Iudocus+Hondius%2C+woonende+op+den+Dam+%26%2391%3Bliving+on+the+Dam%26%2393%3B&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F51084257&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43">[43]</a></sup></li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHues1624" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1624), <i>Tractatvs de globis, coelesti et terrestri eorvmqve vsv [Treatise on Globes, Celestial and Terrestrial, and their Use]</i>, Amsterdam: Excudebat [Printed by] H[enricus] Hondius, <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/8909075">8909075</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatvs+de+globis%2C+coelesti+et+terrestri+eorvmqve+vsv+%5BTreatise+on+Globes%2C+Celestial+and+Terrestrial%2C+and+their+Use%5D&amp;rft.date=1624&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Amsterdam&amp;rft.pub=Excudebat+%5BPrinted+by%5D+H%5Benricus%5D+Hondius&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F8909075&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (in Latin).</li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHues1627" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1627), <i>Tractatus duo mathematici: Quorum primus de globis coelesti et terrestri, eorum usu [Two Mathematical Treatises: Of which the First One is about the Celestial and Terrestial Globes, and their Use]</i>, Frankfurt: Bryana, <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/179907636">179907636</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatus+duo+mathematici%3A+Quorum+primus+de+globis+coelesti+et+terrestri%2C+eorum+usu+%5BTwo+Mathematical+Treatises%3A+Of+which+the+First+One+is+about+the+Celestial+and+Terrestial+Globes%2C+and+their+Use%5D&amp;rft.date=1627&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Frankfurt&amp;rft.pub=Bryana&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F179907636&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHuesNottnagel1627" class="citation">Hues, Robert; Nottnagel, Christoph (1627), <i>Tractatus duo quorum primus de globis coelesti et terrestri, eorum usu, \xc3\xa0 Roberto Hues, Anglo, conscriptus. Alter breviarium totius orbis Terrarum, Petri Bertii. Nunc primum luci commi\xc3\x9fi [Two Treatises of which the First One is about the Celestial and Terrestial Globes, and their Use, signed by Robert Hues, Englishman. The Other One is an Anthology of Countries of the Whole World, by Peter Bertius. Now for the first time here gathered.]</i> (3rd ed.), Wittenberg: [s.n.], <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/257661113">257661113</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.au=Nottnagel%2C+Christoph&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatus+duo+quorum+primus+de+globis+coelesti+et+terrestri%2C+eorum+usu%2C+%C3%A0+Roberto+Hues%2C+Anglo%2C+conscriptus.+Alter+breviarium+totius+orbis+Terrarum%2C+Petri+Bertii.+Nunc+primum+luci+commi%C3%9Fi+%5BTwo+Treatises+of+which+the+First+One+is+about+the+Celestial+and+Terrestial+Globes%2C+and+their+Use%2C+signed+by+Robert+Hues%2C+Englishman.+The+Other+One+is+an+Anthology+of+Countries+of+the+Whole+World%2C+by+Peter+Bertius.+Now+for+the+first+time+here+gathered.%5D&amp;rft.date=1627&amp;rft.edition=3rd&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Wittenberg&amp;rft.pub=%5Bs.n.%5D&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F257661113&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHues1634" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1634), <i>Tractatvs de Globis Coelesti et Terrestri eorvmqve vsv: Primum conscriptus &amp; editus \xc3\xa0 Roberto Hues Anglo semelque atque iteram \xc3\xa0 Iudoco Hondio excusus, &amp; nunc elegantibus iconibus &amp; figuris locupletatus: ac de novo recognitus multisque observationibus oportun\xc3\xa8 illustratus ac passim auctus opera ac studio. Iohannis Isacii Pontani Medici &amp; Philosophi\xc3\xa6 Professoris in Gymnasio Gelrico Hardervici [Treatise on Globes, Celestial and Terrestrial, and their Use. First Written and Published by Robert Hues, Englishman, and in the First and Second Editions Drawn by Jodocus Hondius, and now Enlarged by Elegant Pictures and Drawings, and again Revised and Fittingly Illustrated by Many Observations, and throughout Enlarged by the Work and Effort of John Isaac Pontanus, Physician and Professor of Philosophy of the School in Harderwijk]</i>, Amsterdam: Excudebat Henricus Hondius, sub signo Canis Vigilantis in Platea Vitulina prope Senatorium [Printed by Henricus Hondius, under the sign of the Watchful Dog in Calf Street [<a href="/wiki/Kalverstraat" title="Kalverstraat">Kalverstraat</a>] near the council hall]</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatvs+de+Globis+Coelesti+et+Terrestri+eorvmqve+vsv%3A+Primum+conscriptus+%26+editus+%C3%A0+Roberto+Hues+Anglo+semelque+atque+iteram+%C3%A0+Iudoco+Hondio+excusus%2C+%26+nunc+elegantibus+iconibus+%26+figuris+locupletatus%3A+ac+de+novo+recognitus+multisque+observationibus+oportun%C3%A8+illustratus+ac+passim+auctus+opera+ac+studio.+Iohannis+Isacii+Pontani+Medici+%26+Philosophi%C3%A6+Professoris+in+Gymnasio+Gelrico+Hardervici+%5BTreatise+on+Globes%2C+Celestial+and+Terrestrial%2C+and+their+Use.+First+Written+and+Published+by+Robert+Hues%2C+Englishman%2C+and+in+the+First+and+Second+Editions+Drawn+by+Jodocus+Hondius%2C+and+now+Enlarged+by+Elegant+Pictures+and+Drawings%2C+and+again+Revised+and+Fittingly+Illustrated+by+Many+Observations%2C+and+throughout+Enlarged+by+the+Work+and+Effort+of+John+Isaac+Pontanus%2C+Physician+and+Professor+of+Philosophy+of+the+School+in+Harderwijk%5D&amp;rft.date=1634&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Amsterdam&amp;rft.pub=Excudebat+Henricus+Hondius%2C+sub+signo+Canis+Vigilantis+in+Platea+Vitulina+prope+Senatorium+%5BPrinted+by+Henricus+Hondius%2C+under+the+sign+of+the+Watchful+Dog+in+Calf+Street+%26%2391%3BKalverstraat%26%2393%3B+near+the+council+hall%5D&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44">[44]</a></sup> Collection of the <a href="/wiki/Biblioteca_Nacional_de_Portugal" title="Biblioteca Nacional de Portugal">Biblioteca Nacional de Portugal</a>.</li>\n<li><cite id="CITEREFHues1651" class="citation">Hues, Robert (1651), <i>Tractatus duo mathematici. Quorum primus de globis coelesti et terrestri, eorum usu, a Roberto Hues&#160;... conscriptus. Alter breviarium totius orbis terrarum, Petri Bertii&#160;... Editio prioribus auctior &amp; emendatior [Two Mathematical Treatises. Of which the First One is about the Celestial and Terrestial Globes, and their Use, signed&#160;... Robert Hues. The Other One an Anthology of Countries of the Whole World, of Peter Bertius&#160;... First enlarged &amp; improved edition]</i>, Oxford: Excudebat [Printed by] L. Lichfield, impensis [at the expense of] Ed. Forrest, <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/14913709">14913709</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Hues&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Hues&amp;rft.btitle=Tractatus+duo+mathematici.+Quorum+primus+de+globis+coelesti+et+terrestri%2C+eorum+usu%2C+a+Roberto+Hues+...+conscriptus.+Alter+breviarium+totius+orbis+terrarum%2C+Petri+Bertii+...+Editio+prioribus+auctior+%26+emendatior+%5BTwo+Mathematical+Treatises.+Of+which+the+First+One+is+about+the+Celestial+and+Terrestial+Globes%2C+and+their+Use%2C+signed+...+Robert+Hues.+The+Other+One+an+Anthology+of+Countries+of+the+Whole+World%2C+of+Peter+Bertius+...+First+enlarged+%26+improved+edition%5D&amp;rft.date=1651&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Excudebat+%5BPrinted+by%5D+L.+Lichfield%2C+impensis+%5Bat+the+expense+of%5D+Ed.+Forrest&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F14913709&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>, two pts. Collection of the <a href="/wiki/Bodleian_Library" title="Bodleian Library">Bodleian Library</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Robert_Hues&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span